### Test Async Approval Queue Implementation
### Prerequisites: 
### 1. Run migration: dotnet ef database update --project TextToSqlAgent.Infrastructure --startup-project TextToSqlAgent.API
### 2. Start API: dotnet run --project TextToSqlAgent.API
### 3. Get auth token from login endpoint
### 4. Replace {{token}} and {{connectionId}} below

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
@connectionId = YOUR_CONNECTION_ID_HERE

### 1. Test Write Operation (should create approval queue entry)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/process/stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Insert a new customer named John Doe with email john@example.com",
  "connectionId": "{{connectionId}}",
  "conversationId": null
}

### Expected Response:
### - SSE stream with approval_created event
### - Response includes approvalId
### - No blocking "Waiting for approval..." message

###

### 2. Get Pending Approvals
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "count": 1,
###   "approvals": [
###     {
###       "id": "abc123def456",
###       "question": "Insert a new customer...",
###       "operationType": "INSERT",
###       "targetTable": "Customers",
###       "sqlStatement": "INSERT INTO...",
###       "estimatedRows": 1,
###       "riskLevel": "LOW",
###       "createdAt": "2026-04-12T...",
###       "timeoutAt": "2026-04-12T..." (4 hours later)
###     }
###   ]
### }

###

### 3. Get Specific Approval
@approvalId = APPROVAL_ID_FROM_STEP_2
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/{{approvalId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4. Approve and Execute SQL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/{{approvalId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "modifiedSql": null
}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "message": "Approval accepted - executing SQL in background",
###   "approvalId": "abc123def456",
###   "status": "executing"
### }

###

### 5. Approve with Modified SQL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/{{approvalId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "modifiedSql": "INSERT INTO Customers (Name, Email) VALUES ('Jane Doe', 'jane@example.com')"
}

###

### 6. Reject Approval
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/{{approvalId}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "SQL looks incorrect - wrong table"
}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "message": "Approval rejected",
###   "approvalId": "abc123def456",
###   "status": "rejected"
### }

###

### 7. Check Approval Status After Execution (wait 2-3 seconds)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/{{approvalId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "id": "abc123def456",
###   "status": "completed",
###   "executedAt": "2026-04-12T...",
###   "executionResult": "{\"success\":true,\"affectedRows\":1,...}",
###   "affectedRows": 1
### }

###

### 8. Test Timeout (create approval and wait 4+ hours - or modify TimeoutAt in DB)
### Manual test: Update TimeoutAt to past time in database
### Then run background worker or wait 1 minute for it to run
### Check status should be "timeout"

###

### 9. Test Multiple Concurrent Approvals
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/process/stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Update customer email to newemail@example.com where id = 1",
  "connectionId": "{{connectionId}}"
}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/process/stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Delete from Orders where status = 'cancelled'",
  "connectionId": "{{connectionId}}"
}

### Then check pending approvals - should see multiple entries
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 10. Test Error Handling - Invalid Approval ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/invalid-id-12345
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 404 Not Found

###

### 11. Test Error Handling - Approve Already Approved
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/approvals/{{approvalId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "modifiedSql": null
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - "Cannot approve - status is approved/completed"

###

### 12. Test User Isolation - Try to access another user's approval
### (Need to get approval ID from another user's session)
### Expected: 404 Not Found (user validation)
